  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Therefore whatsoever ye have spoken in darkness,.... In the most private manner, to one another: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "shall be heard in the light; which makes all things manifest, the day shall declare it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and that which ye have spoken in the ear in closets; whispered to persons in their bedchambers, and places of the most secret retirement; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "shall be proclaimed upon the housetops; declared in the most public manner: in Matthew 10:27 these words are so expressed, as to carry in them such a sense as this; that what was told the disciples by Christ, in the most private place and way, should be published by them, in the most free and open manner; See Gill on Matthew 10:27. ",
