        "text": "Closets (ταμείοις)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The word has the same root as: τέμνω, to cut or divide, and means an apartment where supplies are divided and apportioned: a treasury, magazine, and therefore a secret and well-guarded place. There the steward (ταμίας), the distributor, has his seat.",
